Docker Installation Guide for Windows

1. Download Docker Desktop

Open:

[Docker Desktop Download Page](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/)

Click:

>> Download for Windows

---

2. Run Installer

Open the downloaded `.exe` file.

Keep these options checked:

- ✅ Use WSL 2 instead of Hyper-V
- ✅ Add shortcut to desktop

Click:

>> OK / Install

---

3. Restart Computer

Restart if Docker asks.

---

4. Start Docker Desktop

Open:

- Docker Desktop

Wait until:

>> Docker Desktop is running

appears.

---

5. Install WSL2 (If Required)

Open PowerShell as Administrator

Search:

>> PowerShell

Right-click → Run as Administrator

---

Install WSL

PowerShell (Admin): >> wsl --install

Wait for installation.

Then restart your PC.

---

Check WSL Status

PowerShell: >> wsl --status

If working, you will see WSL information.

---

Set WSL2 Default

PowerShell: >> wsl --set-default-version 2

---

6. Enable Required Windows Features

Run these commands in Administrator PowerShell:

PowerShell (Admin): >> dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart

PowerShell (Admin): >> dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart

Restart PC again.

---

7. Enable Virtualization in BIOS

If WSL still fails:

- Restart PC
- Open BIOS/UEFI

Enable:

- Intel VT-x
- AMD-V
- Virtualization Technology

Then save and restart.

---

8. Verify Docker Installation

CMD / PowerShell: >> docker --version

Example:

>> Docker version 28.x.x

---

9. Test Docker

CMD / PowerShell: >> docker run hello-world

If Docker works, you will see a success message.

---

10. Run Ubuntu Container

CMD / PowerShell: >> docker run -it ubuntu

You will enter Ubuntu terminal:

>> root@container-id:/#

---

11. Test WSL

PowerShell / CMD: >> wsl

or

PowerShell / CMD: >> wsl -l -v

