=> Useful Docker Commands

docker pull ubuntu						        → Download Ubuntu image

docker run -it ubuntu						        → Run Ubuntu container

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

=> Basic Linux Commands Inside Docker Container

ls									        → List files and folders

pwd									        → Show current directory

mkdir test								        → Create folder

touch file.txt								        → Create file

cat file.txt								        → Display file content

echo "Hello" > file.txt						        → Write into file

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

exit									        → Exit container

docker ps								        → Show running containers

docker ps -a								        → Show all containers

docker stop <container_id>					        → Stop container

docker rm <container_id>					        → Remove container

docker images								        → Show downloaded images

docker rmi <image_name>						        → Remove image

docker rmi -f <image_name>					        → Force remove image

---------------------------------[ EXTRA ]----------------------------------------------
docker start -ai <container_id>				        → Start existing container

docker exec -it <container_id> bash			        → Open terminal inside container

